                   "message":  "EDITOR-WORLD-SWAP: runtime EditorShell::replace_world substrate\n\nAdd a runtime surface to replace the live editor World after construction,\nresetting the shell to the load-only baseline `with_world` produces. This is\nthe substrate under in-app scene Open (the Ctrl+O wiring is a follow-up\ndispatch). Substrate only; no binary changes.\n\n`EditorShell::replace_world(\u0026mut self, world: rge_kernel_ecs::World) -\u003e\nResult\u003c(), String\u003e`, Editing-gated:\n- installs the new kernel world into a fresh wrapper (TimeScale-if-absent);\n- clears CAD-mode fields (cad_world / projection / cad_graph / cad_entity);\n- clears render content (prebuilt_render_* + GPU meshes/materials + highlight)\n  so the viewport renders blank — encode_main_pass skips an empty mesh set,\n  matching the --scene load-only semantics;\n- drops the PIE snapshot, resets selection (coord);\n- installs a fresh CommandBus so an old-world undo/redo can never replay\n  against the new kernel world;\n- clears glb_source_path (swapped-in world has no GLB hot-reload source),\n  preserving reload_hook / open_dialog so Ctrl+O / R-key stay wired.\n\nPreserves the GPU context, camera, PlayState, audit ledger, tick counter.\nnotify-watcher teardown is the binary\u0027s concern (dispatch 2, reacting to the\nnow-None glb_source_path).\n\n6 headless tests: new-world install + non-CAD, CAD-mode clear, render-mesh\nblank, Editing-gate rejection, CommandBus dirty-\u003eclean reset, glb_source clear\nwith hooks preserved.\n\nCodex pre-exec review: NEEDS_CORRECTION -\u003e CORRECT (reset command_bus + clear\nglb_source_path) -\u003e approved to execute.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
